A4.text: Prélude à l'Après-midi d'un faune (L. 86), known in English as Prelude to the Afternoon of a Faun, is a symphonic poem for orchestra by Claude Debussy, approximately 10 minutes in duration.

A5.text: It was composed in 1894 and first performed in Paris on 22 December 1894, conducted by Gustave Doret.
